Provides a way to look up the property group type identifiers and property type identifiers for the system-defined item type named "Stored Query".

Since:
4.0

SERIALIZED_SEARCH_TYPE

public static final StoredQueryPropertyTypeId SERIALIZED_SEARCH_TYPE
The "Serialized Search Type" property type of the "Stored Query" item type.

A property of this type indicates the kind of query being stored, and the syntax (stored in SERIALIZED_SEARCH_STRING or SERIALIZED_SEARCH_XML) being used to store it.

SERIALIZED_SEARCH_STRING

public static final StoredQueryPropertyTypeId SERIALIZED_SEARCH_STRING
The search, serialized as a single string. The exact syntax, and whether this value is expected to be present at all, is dependent on the value of SERIALIZED_SEARCH_TYPE.

SERIALIZED_SEARCH_XML

public static final StoredQueryPropertyTypeId SERIALIZED_SEARCH_XML

PRESENTATION_STATE_GROUP

public static final StoredQueryPropertyTypeId PRESENTATION_STATE_GROUP
The (optional) "Presentation State" property group type of the "Stored Query" item type.

The properties in a group of this type describe (to a client) how best to present the search to the user. There can be zero or more groups of this type, to provide hints to multiple kinds of client.

PRESENTATION_STATE_TYPE

public static final StoredQueryPropertyTypeId PRESENTATION_STATE_TYPE
The "Type" property type of the "Presentation State" property group type of the "Stored Query" item type.

A property of this type indicates the presentation syntax for the search (stored in PRESENTATION_STATE_STRING or PRESENTATION_STATE_XML).

PRESENTATION_STATE_STRING

public static final StoredQueryPropertyTypeId PRESENTATION_STATE_STRING
A description of how to present the search to the user, serialized as a single string. The exact syntax, and whether this value is expected to be present at all, is dependent on the value of PRESENTATION_STATE_TYPE.
